gomodel:SYNGO_2207  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"In homogenates prepared from neurons in primary culture, WWL70 inhibited ~50% of the total [3H]-2-AG hydrolysis (Fig. 2d)\"\n\nIn cortical layer 5 pyramidal neurons, inhibition of ABDH6 promotes induction of CB1-dependent long-term depression (eCB-LTD) at excitatory synapses using a subthreshold stimulation protocol (Figure 6). This effect is blocked by the CB1 receptor antagonist AM251 demonstrating the action of 2-AG on the presynaptic CB1 receptor (Figure 6).\n\nIn cultured neurons, 2-AG hydrolysis under basal or stimulated conditions significantly decreases upon inhibition of ABDH6 activity using WWL70 (Figure 3, Supplementary Figure 4).\n\n15/12/2017 Pim\n- The retrograde transsynaptic signaling aspect of the endocanabiniod signaling in the preparation featured in this paper has been shown in another paper (PMID:17684555): \"Sub-threshold stimulation of pyramidal neurons in layer 2 of this brain area induces eCB-dependent LTD (eCB-LTD) in layer 5 when a non-specific inhibitor of 2-AG hydrolysis, URB602, is added.\". Experimental description: Electron microscopy: C57BL/6 mice; adulte, cortical layers 4-5 (Fig 5)\nCell type and synapse type immunostaining: C57BL/6 mouse cortical sections (sup. Fig 9)\nneuronal culture: Mouse neurons and microglia in primary culture...Briefly, for neurons,\none day-old mouse brains (C57BL/6) were collected, and their meninges and cerebellum removed. The remaining brain tissue was chopped and the cells dissociated and plated in 10-cm dishes...\nElectrophysiology: Mouse brain slices (C57BL/6, ~8 wks old, 300 μm) were prepared as described32. In brief, immediately after cutting, slices containing the prefrontal cortex were stored for ~30 min...." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2207" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

